Subject: [PATCH 0001/0004] relax frame-ancestors so pan-agent Tauri shell can iframe Claw3D

The pan-agent desktop application is a Tauri v2 shell running on
tauri://localhost (prod) or http://localhost:5173 (Vite dev). Claw3D
upstream ships Content-Security-Policy with "frame-ancestors 'self'",
which blocks that iframe. Also relax X-Frame-Options which is legacy and
conflicts with frame-ancestors when both are set.

The pan-agent Go gateway (also on port 8642) serves both the bundle AND
the WebSocket adapter, so permitting http://localhost:8642 as an ancestor
covers the "user opens the bundle in a plain browser" case.

---
 next.config.ts | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/next.config.ts b/next.config.ts
--- a/next.config.ts
+++ b/next.config.ts
@@ -6,7 +6,7 @@ const securityHeaders = [
       "default-src 'self'",
       "base-uri 'self'",
       "form-action 'self'",
-      "frame-ancestors 'self'",
+      "frame-ancestors 'self' tauri://localhost http://localhost:5173 http://localhost:8642",
       "img-src 'self' data: blob: http: https:",
       "font-src 'self' data: https:",
       "style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https:",
@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@ const securityHeaders = [
   },
   {
     key: "X-Frame-Options",
-    value: "SAMEORIGIN",
+    value: "ALLOW-FROM http://localhost:5173",
   },
   {
     key: "Permissions-Policy",
